            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1706628515077-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced green chilli</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>cider</strong> <strong>vinegar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside – this is your <strong>quick-pickled chilli</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1706628518949-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1706628518949-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1706628518949-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1706628518949-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1706628518949-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> <strong>mix</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>kidney</strong> <strong>beans</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>sweet</strong> <strong>potato</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling</strong> <strong>film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 5-6 min or until the sweet potato is fork-tender, then crush lightly with a fork</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1706628522966-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1706628522966-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1706628522966-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1706628522966-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1706628522966-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>onion</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1706628527237-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1706628527237-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1706628527237-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1706628527237-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1706628527237-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1706628532194-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1706628532194-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1706628532194-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1706628532194-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1706628532194-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> to the pan with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked</strong> <strong>paprika</strong>, <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong> and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1706628536175-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1706628536175-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1706628536175-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1706628536175-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1706628536175-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>drained kidney beans</strong> with the <strong>stock</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Stir through the <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>sweet</strong> <strong>potato</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 8-10 min, stirring occasionally or until the sauce has thickened – this is your<strong> sweet potato & bean chilli</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1706628539511-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1706628539511-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1706628539511-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1706628539511-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1706628539511-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sweet potato & bean chilli </strong>over the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>cheese</strong> and <strong>quick-pickled</strong> <strong>chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Skip the quick-pickled chilli!</span></strong></p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt</strong> if needed</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
